worldborder-fabric.duskconfig.title: World Border Config
worldborder-fabric.duskconfig.DESC_enabl: When enabled, uses the overworldBorderCoords to set the border.
When enabled, uses the netherBorderCoords to set the border.
When enabled, uses the endBorderCoords to set the border.
worldborder-fabric.duskconfig.DESC_shoul: When enabled, instead of teleporting the player inside near where they were, teleports them from the positive to the negative x/z coord and vice versa.
worldborder-fabric.duskconfig.DESC_dista: The amount of blocks the player is teleported inside after hitting the border.
worldborder-fabric.duskconfig.DESC_nearB: The message which will be sent to the player when they are within 'distanceTeleportedBack' to the world border.
worldborder-fabric.duskconfig.DESC_hitBo: The message which will be sent to the player when they hit the world border.
worldborder-fabric.duskconfig.DESC_loopB: The message sent to the player when they hit the border and 'shouldLoopToOppositeBorder' is enabled.
worldborder-fabric.duskconfig.DESC_overw: The overworld border located at the positive x coordinate.
The overworld border located at the negative x coordinate.
The overworld border located at the positive z coordinate.
The overworld border located at the negative z coordinate.
worldborder-fabric.duskconfig.DESC_nethe: The nether border located at the positive x coordinate.
The nether border located at the negative x coordinate.
The nether border located at the positive z coordinate.
The nether border located at the negative z coordinate.
worldborder-fabric.duskconfig.DESC_endBo: The end border located at the positive x coordinate.
The end border located at the negative x coordinate.
The end border located at the positive z coordinate.
The end border located at the negative z coordinate.
